{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Cache keys generated from identical query parameters are always identical, and keys from different parameters never collide.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Failure boundary is the key-derivation function itself (canonicalization, ordering, hashing/encoding). No I/O is required. A pure mock is not needed and does not add coverage; real failures are deterministic logic errors inside one local boundary.","test_description":"Unit-test the key builder with parameter permutations (same semantic params in different orders) and assert identical keys; run a broad corpus/property test over distinct parameter sets and assert no collisions within the tested domain.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The TTL for a cache entry is computed correctly based on the data category's configured freshness rule.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"TTL mapping from category+config to duration is deterministic business logic. No OS/network/subprocess dependency is required if config/time source is injected. Mocking does not hide the core failure; wrong rule selection or unit conversion is local logic.","test_description":"Unit-test TTL computation with a fixed config fixture (e.g., `user_profiles=300s`, `product_catalog=3600s`) and assert exact durations for each category, including unknown/default category handling.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.88,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When memory usage exceeds the configured threshold, the eviction strategy switches from LRU to LFU as specified in the configuration.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure is often at module wiring: memory-pressure source + config threshold + strategy selector. A unit test